rComments: Lectures were generally strong and well-organized and covered a decent breadth of material. However, severe lack of support outside of class; very few office hours, extremely slow responses to email (if any), no course website, and otherwise hard to obtain clarification. Yes, he seems arrogant, but overall okay course if you only expect lectures.

I completely agree with the comment below. Wesley Wark is one of the most pretentious professors I have met on campus. He puts videos of himself up for us to watch in class, he is redundant during his lectures, BORING, NOT helpful, and takes vacations during the school year--he missed a class due to that. Overall, crap experience

Love this class, and loved Wark. He got more and more friendly and jovial as the year went on, but never lost his passion for the topic. I admit to having spy fantasies about him during class.
Especially helpful with my essay (which was a disaster), which meant I didn't give up when I had been tempted to. He expects alot from students, but proved willing to give alot in return.

Wark was one of the best reasons to go to U of T. Of course I took his course right after 9/11 happened, which made it even cooler, but his lectures were always fascinating and he is pretty helpful.
